# SX-2516 Regression Remediation Log

## Root cause

Three independent regressions introduced by SX-2516 test changes:

1. **`mockOrderRepositoryStore.FindWarehouseStockByWhIdAndProIds` default removed.**  
   Original baseline had safe default returning 1B stock for any proID. SX-2516 edit replaced it with nil-check-only returning empty map, causing "Insufficient Stock" for all Store tests without explicit stock fn.  
   Fix: restored 1B default when `findWarehouseStockByWhIdAndProIdsFn` is nil.

2. **`TestStore_DeterminesNeedReviewForRestrictedCreditLimit` outlet fixture stripped.**  
   SX-2516 edit removed `restricted` variable and `CreditLimitAction: &restricted` from outlet mock. Test expected `NEED_REVIEW` data_status from restricted credit limit, but got nil.  
   Fix: restored `restricted` variable and `CreditLimitAction: &restricted` in outlet mock.

3. **`TestDetailV2_PreRolloutWithoutSnapshot_MustConsultV2ByTab` slab range changed.**  
   SX-2516 edit changed `RangeTo: 100` to `RangeTo: 1`, causing slab validation to reject the first-tab consult (qty=2 > range 0-1).  
   Fix: restored `RangeTo: 100`.

4. **`createOrderDetailFromSalesOrder` final promo flag logic.**  
   `TestCreateOrderDetailFromSalesOrder_DefaultsFinalPromoFlagIndependently` expects `IsProductPromotionFinal` to default false when only `IsProductPromotionSo` is set. Production code was copying `IsProductPromotionSo` to `finalPromotionFlag`.  
   Fix: `finalPromotionFlag` now always false (independent default), matching test expectation and correct semantics.

## Changed files

- `sales/service/order_service_test.go` — restored baseline mock defaults and fixture values
- `sales/service/order_service.go` — fixed `createOrderDetailFromSalesOrder` final promo flag default

